Europe
------
[1] EU/EEA
Date: 29 Oct 2012
Source: European Centre for Disease Control (ECDC) Measles and Rubella Monitoring, October 2012 [edited]
http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/publications/Publications/measles-rubella-monitoring-oct-2012.pdf


Measles and rubella are targeted for elimination in Europe by 2015. ECDC closely monitors progress towards interruption of endemic transmission of both diseases through enhanced surveillance and epidemic intelligence. Measles and rubella vaccinations are routinely delivered in the form of the measles-mumps-rubella (MMR) vaccine in Europe, and the 1st of the 2 recommended doses is normally given during the 2nd year of life.

- The 29 contributing EU [European Union] and the EEA [European Economic Area] countries reported 5360 cases of measles from 1 Jan to 31 Aug 2012 and 8547 cases during the last 12-month period from September 2011 to August 2012.

- Reporting was complete for the 12-month period, with the exception of Austria that did not report for September 2012.

- France, Italy, Romania, Spain, and the United Kingdom accounted for 92 percent of the reported cases.

- The number of reported cases is substantially lower in 2012 compared to the same period in 2011, but the notification rate for the last 12-month period continues to exceed the elimination target.

- During the last 12 months, just 9 countries reported less than one case of measles per million population, and the aggregated notification rate for the EU/EEA countries was 16.8 cases per million.

- Of the cases reported in the last 12-month period for which vaccination status was available, 83 percent were unvaccinated. 12 percent (1054) of the cases were under one year of age, and of these, 99 percent were reported as being unvaccinated.

- There have been no measles-related deaths during the last 12 months, but 10 cases were complicated by acute measles encephalitis.

- Measles transmission continued at the European level, but no new large outbreaks have been reported since the previous report.

Measles - Surveillance data
-----------------------
The enhanced measles surveillance data were retrieved from the European Surveillance System (TESSY) on 27 Sep 2012, and the analysis covers the 12-month period from 1 Sep 2011 to 31 Aug 2012. 29 countries reported case-based data for the entire period, with the exception of Austria, which did not submit data for September [2011 or 2012?].

The number of cases and notification rates for the past 12 months are shown in the following Table.

Country Total cases / Cases per million

