[Romania heads the list, followed closely by Ireland, Spain, and the United Kingdom. Iceland is the only European country of the 29 listed to be free of measles virus infection. - Mod.CP]

******
[2] Ukraine
Date: Fri 9 Nov 2023
Source: Unn.com.ua, [in Russian, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://www.unn.com.ua/ru/news/1021301-za-nedelyu-v-ukraine-zaregistrirovali-57-sluchaev-podozreniya-zabolevaniya-koryu


Since the beginning of the year [2012], 12 281 cases of measles have been recorded in Ukraine. During the past week (up to 31 Oct 2012), a total of 57 suspected measles cases has been registered, mostly in the western region of Ukraine, namely 12 in Lvov region, 6 in Ternopil region, 5 in Volyn region, and 11 in Kiev region. According to the regional medical authorities, overall, approximately 18 000 Ukrainians may have contracted measles.

The increase in measles cases has been attributed to incomplete vaccine coverage. Measles is a vaccine-preventable disease, and measles vaccine should be administered at one year, 6 years, and again at 12-15 years of age. Those aged 29-30 years of age are at greatest risk, since their (innate) immunity may have declined in the absence of revaccination, according to O. Nazar, chief immunologist in the Kiev region.

--
